# Algorithm Design

## Optimization Model

The following optimization model is assumed to be run on the H3/store level. Therefore, only H3 level capacity is considered. If we need to run the optimization model on H2/store or H1/store level, the model would be the same. However, it shall require constraints that specify minimum number of SKUs to include in the assortment for deeper levels of the hierarchy.

### Inputs

P_{ij} : substitution probability from SKU i to SKU j

D_{i} : forecasted demand for SKU i

p_{i} : Unit price (revenue maximization) or unit profit (profit maximization) for SKU i

### Variables

x_{i} :  1 if SKU i is in the assortment, 0 otherwise

y_{ij} : 1 if demand of SKU j substitutes to SKU i, i.e. when SKU i is in the assortment and SKU j is not. Basically, it is 1 when x_{i}(1-x_{j}) is 1, 0 otherwise.

### Model

max z = ∑_{i} p_{i} ( D_{i} x_{i} + ∑_{j, j!=i} D_{j} P_{ji} y_{ij})

s.t.

∑_{i} x_{i} <= C

Model

max z = ∑_{i} p_{i} ( D_{i} x_{i} + ∑_{j, j!=i} D_{j} P_{ji} y_{ij})

s.t.

∑_{i} x_{i} <= C

y_{ij} >= x_{i} - x{j}           for all i, j, i!=j

y_{ij} <= x_{i}                   for all i, j, i!=j

y_{ij} <= 1-x_{j}                for all i, j, i!=j

x_{i}, y_{ij}: binary

### Discussion

Core assortment can easily be added by adding a constraint forcing x_{i} to 1 for products in the core assortment.

Mutually exclusive items can also be incorporated easily. For instance, if SKU 1 and SKU 2 are mutually exclusive, we simply add the following constraint: x_{1} + x_{2} <=1

# Number of Cluster Selection Method

Default*defined maximum of clusters* is 5 in the settings.

It changes with the size of the products in the H3. General Rule is, there should be at least 10 products in each cluster (*NumberOfProducts)* .

The General Rule -> *MaxClusterLimit*: min(floor(*NumberOfProducts* / 10), *defined maximum of clusters*).

While it comes to selecting number of clusters, we try all clustering combinations starting from 1 cıluster to *MaxClusterLimit;*then we select best clustering according to Gap Statistic for Estimating the Number of Clusters using cluster::clusGaP function in R.
